## Tool Tips

- `archiver_read`: Parse natural language time references —
  "last hour", "yesterday", "since Monday" — into start_time/end_time.
- `execute`: Lives on the `python` server. Default to `execution_mode: "readonly"`;
  use `"write"` only when the code needs to write to the control system.
{% if "ariel" not in disable_servers -%}
- `entry_create`: Creates logbook entries directly. Pass `artifact_ids` to attach
  artifacts — HTML artifacts are auto-converted to PNG.
{% endif -%}

## Context Management

- Tool results from the current session are in the conversation history
- For large datasets, results are saved to `./osprey-workspace/` — read these files
  when you need to reference previous results
- Channel addresses found earlier in the session can be reused without re-searching

## Session Log

Use `session_log` to diagnose subagent failures and inspect tool call history.
